<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 4:28AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of west central Haskell,
southern McIntosh, northwestern Latimer and Pittsburg Counties
through 515 AM CDT...
At 428 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 5 miles north of Hanna to 5 miles west of
Mcalester to 3 miles southeast of Wardville. Movement was east at 40
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Eufaula...
Hartshorne...                     Krebs...
Kiowa...                          Savanna...
Crowder...                        Alderson...
Canadian...                       Indianola...
Hanna...                          Raiford...
Haywood...                        Vivian...
Blocker...                        Arrowhead State Park...
Mcalester Regional Airport...     Blanco...
Scipio...                         Haileyville...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
